OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778091067
OL,3,CBirmingham resident offers #100 to
OL,4,Cremove 'dumped' rubbish as bin strike
OL,5,Cgoes on
OL,7,FCommissioners were brought in by the
OL,8,FConservative government after the
OL,9,Fcouncil declared effective bankruptcy
OL,10,Fin 2023. Part of their role is to
OL,11,Fimprove industrial relations, though
OL,12,Fsome believe relations have only
OL,13,Fworsened.
OL,15,FITV News Central understands officials
OL,16,Fargued they couldn't include one-off
OL,17,Fcompensation payments in any deal with
OL,18,Fstriking workers, amid fears the
OL,19,Fcouncil could face wider equal pay
OL,20,Fclaims or be unable to afford similar
OL,21,Fpayouts to other staff.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778091067
OL,3,CBirmingham resident offers #100 to
OL,4,Cremove 'dumped' rubbish as bin strike
OL,5,Cgoes on
OL,7,FIn March, Cllr Majid Mahmood, the
OL,8,FCabinet member for Environment and
OL,9,FTransport, said:
OL,11,F"The bin strike in Birmingham has gone
OL,12,Fon for too long. I'm sorry for the
OL,13,Fdisruption this has caused, and I
OL,14,Fwould hope Unite would also want to
OL,15,Fapologise. It isn't good enough and we
OL,16,Fwant to end the dispute.
OL,18,F"But let us be clear, the council has
OL,19,Fmade a series of offers to Unite to
OL,20,Fend the strike, but they have all been
OL,21,Frejected.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778091067
OL,3,CBirmingham resident offers #100 to
OL,4,Cremove 'dumped' rubbish as bin strike
OL,5,Cgoes on
OL,7,F"We are moving ahead with the
OL,8,Fimplementation of the improved waste
OL,9,Fservice this summer, a service that
OL,10,Fhas been poor for too long.
OL,12,F"This will see the rollout of food
OL,13,Fwaste collections from June this year
OL,14,Fon a phased basis, along with the
OL,15,Freturn of improved recycling and green
OL,16,Fwaste collection services.
OL,18,F"This will happen regardless of the
OL,19,Fsituation with industrial action to
OL,20,Fgive the people of Birmingham the
OL,21,Fwaste service they deserve.
OL,26,@tD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/9
